This is the info we received from Pierre on repositories used by Mission Soil: "There is no single fixed repository or platform for Mission Soil. Mission Soil uses Soil Wise (https://soilwise-he.containers.wur.nl/cat/), an online catalogue that provides metadata on soil-related data and knowledge. Soil Wise relies on OpenAire (Open Access Infrastructure for Research in Europe), which includes thousands of repositories registered in OpenDOAR (https://opendoar.ac.uk/), but also includes additional soil-specific or EU repositories (INSPIRE geoportal, CORDIS, ESDAC, Bonares, EJP Soil, PrepSoil, Impact4Soil, FAO Soils portal,EEA Datahub, ISRIC - World Soil Information)." - I wonder if we can just link to Soil Wise at this position or if we need to specify the exact repositories already?


